==English==
=== Noun ===
'''meliorist''' (''plural'' '''meliorists''')
#An individual or group who enjoys controversy by engaging in a reformist stance.
#A proponent of [[meliorism]]

====Etymology====
From {{L.}} [[melior]] ''better'' +[[-ist]]. British author [[w:George Eliot|George Eliot]] is believed to have first coined the term in her letters published in 1877.

=== Adjective ===
'''meliorist''' ('''more meliorist''', '''most meliorist''')
#Of or relating to [[meliorism]].
#Supporting the principles of meliorism.

